# Token Diet Hygiene Checklist

Quick-reference for minimizing per-turn token overhead. For full diagnosis, run `/token-diet`.

## Before Adding an `alwaysApply: true` Rule

- [ ] Does this content truly need to be in EVERY agent turn? If not, use `alwaysApply: false`
- [ ] Is the rule < 2 KB? Rules > 2 KB should be split or trimmed
- [ ] Does an existing rule already cover this? Check for overlap before creating new ones
- [ ] Could this be a project-scoped skill instead of a rule?

## Before Adding to AGENTS.md

- [ ] Is this a workspace-wide fact needed every turn? If domain-specific, use a scoped rule
- [ ] Does the entry duplicate a `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` rule? Deduplicate — one source of truth
- [ ] Is the entry concise? Use bullet fragments, not full sentences

## MCP Server Hygiene

- [ ] Is the MCP server actively used in this project? Disable unused servers
- [ ] Target: ≤ 10 enabled servers per project (each adds ~1000 tokens of schema)

## Skill Description Hygiene

- [ ] Is the `description` field in YAML frontmatter ≤ 512 characters?
- [ ] Does the description use `>-` folded block to avoid accidental whitespace bloat?
- [ ] Are "Do NOT use for" entries concise? One line per exclusion

## Session Cost Awareness

- [ ] Use `fast` model for exploration subagents — 10× cheaper than Sonnet
- [ ] Run `/clear` between unrelated tasks to reset context
- [ ] At logical phase boundaries, consider context compaction (see `ecc-strategic-compact`)
- [ ] Prefix shell commands with `rtk` for 60-90% output compression (see `rtk-token-optimization.mdc`)
